HEADWORD: Howbeit
<hw>How*be"it</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>conj.</pos> <ety>[<ets>How</ets> +
<ets>be</ets> + <ets>it</ets>.]</ety> <def>Be it as it may;
nevertheless; notwithstanding; although; albeit; yet; but;
however.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The Moor -- <qex>howbeit</qex> that I endure him not -⟦br⟧
Is of a constant, loving, noble nature.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

